  "text": "Parent recommendations regarding the timing and content of childhood obesity prevention strategies concur with epidemiological studies: parents suggested that prevention needed to begin before children were at school. With almost onefifth of children already overweight at age five [CITATION_1] , the usual age of school entry, school-based prevention strategies alone are too late to prevent overweight for this population of children. However, school-based strategies may be able to attenuate change over time.",
